| image3=Paris Metro 5.svg | imagesize3=22 | directionl3=N | majorl3=[[Bobigny]] | minorl3='''[[Paris/3rd arrondissement|3rd arrondissement]]''' | directionr3=S | majorr3=[[Paris/13th arrondissement|13th arrondissement]] | minorr3=[[Paris/4th arrondissement|4th arrondissement]] }}
{{usabledistrict}} {{geo|48.8594|2.3794|zoom=14}} {{IsPartOf|Paris}}

{{pagebanner|Paris 12e Wikivoyage Banner.png|pgname=12th arrondissement}} The '''12th arrondissement''' of [[Paris]] is one of the largest of the city's districts even without the 2,460 acre ''Bois de Vincennes'', which more than doubles its size. ''Gare de Lyon'' in the 12th will likely be your arrival point if you are coming from [[Switzerland]], [[Italy]], or the south of [[France]].
==Get in== [[Image:Paris_12th_jardin_rabin.jpg|thumb|250px|The peace fountain in Paris' Jardin Yitzhak Rabin]] {{Mapframe|48.8348|2.4123|height=250|width=350|zoom=12|name=Map of the 12th arrondissement|staticmap=Paris 12th arrondissement map with listings.png}} {{Mapshape}} {{Mapshapes|Q50716}}
===''By Métro''=== ''Métro'', line 14, serves '''Gare de Lyon''' and '''Gare de Bercy'''.
Line 1 crosses the arrondissement east-west serving '''Bastille''', '''Gare de Lyon''', '''Reuilly-Diderot''', '''Nation''', and '''Porte de Vincennes'''.
Line 8 crosses the arrondissement east-west serving '''Bastille''', '''Ledru-Rollin''', '''Faidherbe-Chaligny''', '''Reuilly-Diderot''', '''Montgallet''', '''Daumesnil''', '''Michel Bizot''', '''Porte Dorée''', and '''Porte de Charenton'''.
Line 6 arrives from the left bank, serving '''Bercy''', '''Dugommier''', '''Daumesnil''', '''Bel-Air''', and '''Picpus'''.
The RER-A passes east-west through the 12th serving '''Gare de Lyon''' and '''Nation'''.
==See==
===Landmarks=== * {{see | name=Jardin Yitzhak Rabin | alt= | url= | email= | address= | lat=48.8340 | long=2.3835 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | wikipedia=fr:Jardin Yitzhak-Rabin | image=Paris 12th jardin rabin.jpg | wikidata=Q24932225 | content=Nestled in the centre of the Parc Bercy (below) is a lovely, and truly peaceful, garden with several waterworks and other high-quality landscape-art pieces. If you are one of the many people visiting the 12th on business it would be well worth an hour of your time between meetings and dinner to explore the mound, the fountain, and the bridges, and to watch children play in complete peace, much like the peace to which the garden's namesake dedicated his life. }} * {{see | name=Bercy Village | alt= | url= | email= | address= | lat=48.8331 | long=2.3865 | directions={{station|Cour Saint-Émilion|14}} | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | wikipedia=fr:Bercy Village | image=Bercy Village Cour Saint-Émilion.jpg | wikidata=Q2896969 |lastedit=2022-10-23| content=For a taste of the French countryside, a visit to Bercy Village brings to life the spirit of market shopping inside Paris. }} * {{see | name=AccorHotels Arena | alt= | url=http://www.bercy.fr | email= | address= | lat=48.838653 | long=2.3785 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | wikipedia=AccorHotels Arena | image=AccorHotels Arena @ Bercy @ Paris (27157316713).jpg | wikidata=Q537720 | content=An indoor sports arena that seats around 17,000 for sports and slightly over 20,000 for major concerts; formerly known as ''Palais des Omnisports de Paris-Bercy'' and ''Bercy Arena''. Home to numerous concerts and major sporting events, most notably the Paris Masters tournament on the ATP World Tour in men's tennis. }} * {{see | name=Opéra Bastille | alt= | url=http://www.operadeparis.fr | email= | address=Place de la Bastille | lat=48.851944 | long=2.370556 | directions=Métro Bastille | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | wikipedia=Opéra Bastille | image=Paris-Opera.Bastille-Column-01.jpg | wikidata=Q638423 | content=One of the truly great venues for the performing arts anywhere in the world, Paris' new opera house actually managed to inspire some neighborhood protest during its planning and construction. Pretty much everybody is a believer nowadays though. Check out the website for upcoming shows, it might even make sense to plan a trip to Paris around one. }} * {{see | name=Promenade Plantée | alt=Coulée verte René-Dumont | url=https://en.parisinfo.com/paris-museum-monument/71237/Coulee-verte-Rene-Dumont-ex-Promenade-Plantee | email= | address= | lat=48.849572 | long=2.3711 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | wikipedia=Coulée verte René-Dumont | image=Promenade plantée, Paris August 2009 (10).jpg | wikidata=Q2060889 | content=If you were a city planner in one of the great cities of our Earth and you discovered that a railroad right-of-way had been abandoned and would never be used again what might you do? Perhaps if you knew your stuff you'd convert it into a 4 mile long park, about half of which is elevated above street level on the old rail viaduct. This long narrow park pretty much allows the visitor to walk in carfree bliss from Place de Bastille to the Bois de Vincennes. }} [[File:Paris Parc Bercy Maison du jardinage&massifs 2014.jpg|thumb|Flowerbeds and greenhouse in the Parc de Bercy]] * {{see | name=Parc de Bercy | alt= | url= | email= | address= | lat=48.833889 | long=2.384167 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | wikipedia=Parc de Bercy | image=Les Prairies de Bercy1.jpg | wikidata=Q945251 | content=Between the River Seine and the rail yards attached to ''Gare de Lyon'' and ''Gare de Bercy'' is a green space which would seem pretty huge if the 12th weren't also the home of the ''Bois de Vincennes''. The park is a good place to hang out waiting for the line to form for sporting events and concerts at ''AccorHotels Arena''. }} * {{see | name=Bois de Vincennes | alt= | url=http://www.boisdevincennes.com/ | email= | address= | lat=48.828069 | long=2.432917 | directions=Métro Porte Dorée or Porte de Charenton | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | wikipedia=Bois de Vincennes | image=Bois de Vincennes DSC03761.JPG | wikidata=Q271639 | content=There are many beautiful footpaths, a Buddhist Temple, and a lake with rowboats available for rental (about €10 as of 2009). The lake has many different kinds of birds, and islands accessible by footbridge. }} *{{see | name=Picpus Cemetery | alt=Cimetière de Picpus | url= | email= | address=35 Rue de Picpus | lat=48.843889 | long=2.400278 | directions=Metro Nation | phone=+33 1 43 44 18 54 | tollfree= | hours=Tu-Sa 14:30 | price= | wikipedia=Picpus Cemetery | image=Notre-Dame-de-la-Paix, Paris.JPG | wikidata=Q281477 | content=A must for anyone interested in the history of the [[American Revolution]]. This small cemetery includes three mass graves from the French Revolution, plus a section that includes many of France's most noble families that lost members during the French Revolution and consequently have a continuing right to be buried there. In the farthest right hand corner is the tomb of General Lafayette, the friend and fellow soldier of George Washington. Beside him is his beloved wife plus other members of her family, the de Noailles, who were almost completely wiped out during the French Revolution because of their closeness to the Court. Since 1834 the American flag has apparently flown continuously over his grave, even during the German occupation of Paris during [[World War II]]. Well worthy of a visit. }} * {{see | name=Château de Vincennes | alt= | url=http://www.chateau-vincennes.fr/ | email= | address= | lat=48.842778 | long=2.435833 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | hours= | price= | wikidata=Q663673 | lastedit=2024-10-08 | content=A former fortress and royal residence at the edge of the city, alongside the Bois de Vincennes. Most of the building is open to public. }}
===Museums and galleries=== * {{see | name=Palais de la Porte Dorée | alt= | url= | email= | address=293 avenue Daumesnil | lat=48.835278 | long=2.409444 | directions=Métro: Porte Dorée | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | wikipedia=Palais de la Porte Dorée | image=| wikidata=Q1141316 | content=Housed in an amazing Art Deco building, purpose-built for the 1931 Colonial Exhibition, featuring an elaborate frieze across the front facade that depicts the achievement of French overseas territories. It houses an [http://www.aquarium-portedoree.fr Aquarium] and an [http://www.histoire-immigration.fr Immigration Museum]. The aquarium can be seen in about an hour and is popular with families with small children. }} * {{see | name=Le Musée Fragonard | alt=L'Ecole Nationale Vétérinaire | url=http://musee.vet-alfort.fr | email= | address=7, Avenue du Général de Gaulle | lat=48.8125 | long=2.4226 | directions={{station|École Vétérinaire de Maisons-Alfort}}{{rint|paris|8}} | phone =+33 1 43 96 71 72 | tollfree= | fax= | hours=Closed in Aug; W Th 14:00-18:00; Sa Su 13:00-18:00 | price=Adults €7 | content=This is a hidden gem. A veterinary museum that doubles as natural history museum. A lot of medical oddities, mostly of animals, but also include real human specimens. Move over Bodyworlds, this museum holds Fragonard's original human preservation (wax, not plastic) including the famous "horseman of the apocalypse."}} * {{see | name =Cinema Museum | alt =La Cinémathèque française | url =https://www.cinematheque.fr/ | email = | address =51 Rue de Bercy | lat =48.83725042 | long =2.38252145612 | directions =next to Parc de Bercy, {{station|Bercy|6|14}} | phone = | tollfree = | fax = | hours =Exhibition & Museum M, W-F noon-7PM; Sa-Su 11AM-8PM. closed Tu | price =Exhibition: Adult €12, Reduced €9.50, U18 €6: Museum Adult €10, Reduced&18-35 €7.50, U18 €5. Joint tickets available | wikipedia =Cinémathèque Française | wikidata = | image = | lastedit =2022-10-23 | content =Housed in modern building designed by Frank Gehry, contains a cinema showing French & international films, temporary exhibitions lasting about 6 months, Museum dedicated to the history of cinema. Exhibitions are fairly visual. }}
==Do==
==Buy== There are any number of shops catering to the needs of travellers in and around '''Gare de Lyon''', where you can easily replace a piece of broken luggage or even buy a suit if you suddenly find yourself with a business appointment.
The archways of the former railroad right-of-way which now support the promenade plantée are home to trendy restaurants, designer's studios, and art galleries. Taken as a whole it's known as the ''Viaduc des Arts''', and is well worth a stroll for those interested in art and design.
Another shopping highlight of the 12th is the amazing number of electronics and computer shops, mostly clustered around '''rue Charenton''' near the '''Jardin de Reuilly''', as one would expect the intense competition keeps prices low (for Europe). * {{buy | name=New PC Charenton | url= | email= | address=171 rue de Charenton | lat= | long= | directions= | phone=+33 1 43 07 02 30 | tollfree= | fax= | hours=M-F 10:00-19:00, Sa 09:00-17:00 | price= | content=This is just one example out of the many computer shops in the immediate area, included here to help you find them all. Check the prices here, next door, and across the street. When you find the lowest bidder [[Project:Plunge forward|plunge forward]] and add them here please! }} * {{buy | name=Marché d'Aligre | url= | email= | address= | lat= | long= | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours=Tu-Sa 08:00-13:00 and 16:00-19:30, Su 08:00-13:00 | price= | content=The cheapest open air market in Paris, on Rue d'Aligre. There's produce, carpets, clothes, antiques. Covered market, Marche Beauvau, is adjacent. North African influence, many food shops surround it. }} * {{buy | name=A Carnaval & Fetes | url= | email= | address=22 Av Ladru Rollin | lat= | long= | directions= | phone=+33 1 43 47 06 08 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content= }} * During the spring time there is a carnival called the '''Foire du trône''' held in the Bois de Vincennes
==Eat== * {{eat | name=l'Ébauchoir | url= | email= | address=43-45 rue de Citeaux | lat= | long= | directions=at the corner of rue faubourg Saint Antoine | phone=+33 1 43 42 49 31 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content=A typical restaurant of the bo-bo (bourgeois - bohème) population of this district. Good traditional cooking with mid-range prices. }} * {{eat | name=Refuge | url= | email= | address=54 Avenue Daumesnil | lat= | long= | directions=just around the corner from Gare de Lyon | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price=€15 | content=This charming storefront bistro offers an adventurous take on traditional French cooking, and with a couple of good selections for '''vegetarians''', including a €12 vegetarian ''menu''. The indoor vineyard decor appeals for its artsy clutter; the only indications that the owner and chef is a former rugby star being the newspaper clipping on the wall and the almost hidden world championship medal behind the bar. }} * {{eat | name=Le Train Bleu | url=http://www.le-train-bleu.com/ | email= | address= | lat= | long= | directions=in the 1st floor of Gare de Lyon | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content=Serves haute cuisine in amazing surroundings. Reservations strongly recommended }} *{{eat | name=Le Picotin | url=http://lepicotin.com {{dead link|June 2020|December 2020}} | email= | address=35 rue Sibuet | lat= | long= | directions=Métro: Picpus, Bel-Air | phone=+33 1 46 28 99 00 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price=~€20 main courses | content=An excellent find in a quiet back street. Good value food, with a selection wide enough to offer a good choice whilst allowing the chef to concentrate on perfecting a small number of dishes. Warm, friendly welcome and faultless service. }}
==Drink== *{{drink | name=Café L'Arrosoir | url= | email= | address=75, Avenue Daumesnil | lat= | long= | directions=Métro: Gare de Lyon | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content= }} *{{drink | name=Les Furieux | url= | email= | address=rue de la roquette | lat= | long= | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content=An alternative bar at the end of the Rue de la Roquette, punk, rock, metal, goth. }}
The '''Bastille''' area is quite well known for its many bars and clubs. Among them the '''Barrio Latino''', a large Latin music nightclub on the Rue du Faubourg Saint Antoine.
''Ground Control'' (81 rue du Charolais) is also a nice collection of bars and street food stands based in a converted old rail depot. * {{drink | name=The Frog at Bercy Village | alt= | url=https://www.frogpubs.com/pub-the-frog-at-bercy-village-paris-3.php | email= | address=25 Cour St Emilion | lat=48.83305 | long=2.386064 | directions={{station|Cour St Emilion|14}} | phone=+33 1 43 40 70 71 | tollfree= | hours=Su–Th 10:00–00:00; F Sa 10:00–02:00 | price= | lastedit=2025-06-05 | content=Popular English brew-pub with a French twist. Open terrace at each end. Check the beer menu for current selection of beers brewed on the premises. Interesting range of snacks and more filling dishes. }}
==Sleep==
*{{sleep | name=Hotel de France | alt= | url=http://hotel-defrance-paris.com/ | email= | address=12 rue de Lyon | lat= | long= | directions=Gare de Lyon | phone=+33 1 43 43 0697 | tollfree= | checkin= | checkout= | price=€63-175 | content=Located very close to Gare de Lyon and a short walk from Bastille, it is a decent budget hotel with single, double, triple and quadruple rooms. Convenient to visit Disneyland as well as to the sights of Paris. }} ===Budget=== [[Image:Paris_12th_allee_royal.jpg|thumb|250px|Allée Royal in the Bois de Vincennes]]
* {{sleep | name=Hostel Blue Planet | url=http://www.hostelblueplanet.com/ | email= | address=5 rue Hector Malot | lat= | long= | directions=Métro: Gare de Lyon | phone=+33 1 43 42 06 18 | tollfree= | fax=+33 1 43 42 09 89 | hours= | price=€25 per bed. Towels and sheets extra. | checkin= | checkout= | content=This hostel, within a block of the Gare de Lyon station, has bunk beds in shared rooms sleeping 4-6 people. Some rooms have showers and toilets. A basic breakfast of pastries and hot drinks is included in the price. }} * {{sleep | name=Hôtel Prince Albert | url=http://www.hotelprincealbert.com | email= | address=38 boulevard Diderot | lat= | long= | directions=Métro: Gare de Lyon | phone=+33 1 43 43 54 92 | tollfree= | fax=+33 1 43 47 39 50 | hours= | price= | checkin= | checkout= | content= }} * {{sleep | name=Hôtel de l'Aveyron | url= | email= | address=5 rue d'Austerlitz | lat= | long= | directions=Métro: Gare de Lyon | phone=+33 1 43 07 86 86 | tollfree= | fax=+33 1 43 07 85 20 | hours= | price= | checkin=21.09.2008 | checkout=24.09.2008 | content= }} * {{sleep | name=Hôtel Royal Bel Air | url= | email= | address=10 Avenue du Bel-Air | lat= | long= | directions= | phone=+33 1 43 45 26 00 | tollfree= | fax=+33 1 43 45 98 88 | hours= | price= | checkin= | checkout= | content= }} * {{sleep | name=Corail Hotel | url=http://www.hotel-paris-corail.com | email= | address=23 rue de Lyon | lat= | long= | directions=Métro: Gare de Lyon | phone=+33 1 43 43 23 54 | tollfree= | fax=+33 1 43 43 82 55 | hours= | price= | checkin= | checkout= | content= }} * {{sleep | name=Hotel Le Quartier Bercy - Square | url=http://www.lequartierhotelbs.com | email= | address=33, boulevard de Reuilly | lat= | long= | directions= | phone=+33 1 44 87 09 09 | tollfree= | fax=+33 1 43 07 41 58 | hours= | price= | checkin= | checkout= | content=Hotel Le Quartier Bercy Square, located in the 12th arrondissement, is right between Metro stations Dugommier and Daumesnil (Lines 6 and 8). It has easy access to Palais Omnisports at Bercy, Cours St. Emillon with its lively area of shops, restaurants, and bars, and train stations Gare de Bercy and Gare de Lyon. And with Line 14 at Bercy station just down the road, the rest of Paris is only minutes from you. }} * {{sleep | name=AIJ Paris | alt=Auberge Internationale des Jeunes | url=http://www.aijparis.com/ | email=paris@aijparis.com | address=10, rue trousseau | lat= | long= | directions=Metro: Ledru-Rollin | phone=+33 1 47 00 62 00 | tollfree= | fax= | checkin=15:00 | checkout=11:00 | price=€13-17 | lastedit=2017-10-26 | content=Some sites (including their own) says they are a youth-only hostel, but there do not enforce any age restrictions. Wifi and a small non-buffet continental breakfast is included. Each room has a sink, but the top sheet for each bunk is not included and will cost extra if you don't just want the blanket. No alcohol is allowed in the hostel. The hostel is 24 hr but the rooms close between 11:00-15:00 for cleaning. }}
===Mid-range=== * {{sleep | name=Grand Hôtel Doré | url=http://www.grand-hotel-dore.com/ | email= | address=201 avenue Daumesnil | lat= | long= | directions=Métro: Daumesnil | phone=+33 1 43 43 66 89 | tollfree= | fax=+33 1 43 43 65 20 | hours= | price= | checkin= | checkout= | content=Having opened its doors at the beginning of the 20th century The Grand Hotel Doré has been owned and operated by the same family ever since, giving the place plenty of character and quite a bit of charm. Guests tend to be a pretty even mix of business and pleasure travellers. }} * {{sleep | name=Ibis Gare De Lyon Diderot | alt= | url=https://all.accor.com/hotel/3211/index.en.shtml | email= | address=31 Bis Boulevard Diderot | lat= | long= | directions=Métro: Gare de Lyon, use the side entrance of the station downstairs | phone=+33 1 43 46 12 72 | tollfree= | checkin= | checkout= | price= | content=This branch of the Ibis chain is a bit more comfortable than most, especially worthwhile if you have just arrived at Gare de Lyon. The website has current price information, and links to their 650 sister hotels across Europe. Breakfast (€10, until 10:00) is the pretty ordinary buffet fare. }} * {{sleep | name=Hotel Palym | url=http://www.paris-hotel-palym.com/ | email=infos@hotel-palym.com | address=4, rue Emile Gilbert | lat= | long= | directions= | phone=+33 1 43 43 24 48 | tollfree= | fax=+33 1 43 41 69 47 | hours= | price= | checkin= | checkout= | content=This nice little hotel is around the right price and probably has the closest possible access to the Air France airport buses. }} * {{sleep | name=Hôtel de la Porte Dorée | url=http://www.hoteldelaportedoree.com | email= | address=273, avenue Daumensnil | lat= | long= | directions= | phone=+33 1 43 07 56 97 | tollfree= | fax=+33 1 49 28 08 18 | hours= | price= | checkin= | checkout= | content= }}
===Splurge=== * {{sleep | name=Mercure Paris Gare de Lyon | alt= | url=https://all.accor.com/hotel/2217/index.en.shtml | email= | address=2, place Louis Armand | lat= | long= | directions=Métro: Gare de Lyon | phone=+33 1 43 44 84 84 | tollfree= | fax=+33 1 43 47 41 94 | checkin= | checkout= | price= | content= }} * {{sleep | name=Pullman Paris Bercy | alt=formerly Sofitel Paris Bercy | url=https://all.accor.com/hotel/2192/index.en.shtml | email= | address=1, avenue Terroirs de France | lat= | long= | directions=Métro: Cour St-Emillion | phone=+33 1 44 67 34 00 | tollfree= | fax=+33 1 44 67 34 01 | checkin= | checkout= | price= | content=The former Sofitel was demoted to Pullman, but has since been afforded a thorough renovation (finished in autumn of 2013) to bring it up to current Pullman brand standards along with other Pullman hotels in Paris. Friendly and helpful staff. }}
