| phone=+33 1 40 20 53 17 | tollfree=
| hours=W-M 09:00-18:00, closed public holidays; evening openings W and F until 21:45 | price=€12-16; under 18, free; EU-residents, 18-26 years free; exhibitions in the Hall Napoléon €13; combined ticket (museum + special exhibitions) adults €16 ''Carte Musée''
| wikipedia=Louvre | image=Louvre 2007 02 24 c.jpg | wikidata=Q19675
| content=Its exhibits come from such diverse origins as [[ancient Egypt]], [[classical Greece]] and the [[Roman Empire]], medieval Europe, and Napoleonic France, but controversially including many items that were looted from their places of origin. Its most famous exhibit, of course, is Leonardo da Vinci's painting of the Mona Lisa (French: ''La Joconde'', Italian: ''La Gioconda''), generally to be found surrounded by hordes of camera-flashing tourists. The Louvre poses many of the same challenges to the visitor as Paris itself; overwhelming in size, crowded in high seasons, and much information available only in French. If you want to see everything in the Louvre, plan ''at least'' two full days. However, it is better to pick and choose, as the collection was assembled with an eye to completeness rather than quality. As of July 2019, due to intense crowding and reports of ticket fraud, entry now almost always requires a pre-booked timed ticket, even for holders of the Paris Museum Pass.
}}
