==Eat==
Expect high prices at cafés and restaurants.
=== Budget === * {{eat | name=Chez Germaine | url= | email= | address=30, rue Pierre Leroux | lat= | long= | directions= | phone=+33 1 42 73 28 34 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content=It's all about home-cooking, like your grandma would do if she were French and trained in cooking.}} * {{eat | name=Au Pied de Fouet | alt=At the wrong end of the whip | url= | email= | address=45, rue de Babylone | lat= | long= | directions=Métro: Vaneau | phone=+33 1 47 05 12 27 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price=€8-12 | content=It's an appropriate name for a restaurant renowned for its unapologetically rude wait staff. Some people say that this is part of the charm of the place, perhaps that fits your definition of the word "charm" as well? Or perhaps not. One way or the other it's cheap and the food is good. }}
===Mid-range=== * {{eat | name=Chez l'Ami Jean | url= | email= | address=27 Rue Malar | lat= | long= | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price=Dinner approximately €30, credit cards accepted | content=A sensational little restaurant featuring food and wine from the Basque region.}} * {{eat | name=Le Clos des Gourmets | url= | email= | address=16 avenue Rapp | lat= | long= | directions=Métro: Ecole Militaire / Alma Marceau, RER: Pont de l'Alma | phone=+33 1 45 51 75 61 | tollfree= | fax= | hours=Tu-Sa, 12:15-14:00, 19:15-23:00, Closed Su-M and Aug | price=Dinner menu: €33, credit cards accepted | content=A great little restaurant, elegant without being stuffy, popular with foreign visitors and American diplomatic staff. French cuisine with a twist. Try the avocado millefeuille with orange sauce for dessert, a surprisingly good combination.}} * {{eat | name=Tribeca | url= | email= | address=36, Rue Cler | lat= | long= | directions= | phone=+33 1 45 55 12 01 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price=dinner approximately €20 | content=A very nice terrasse on the rue Cler (pedestrian area). The food is simple, but good and reasonably cheap.}}
=== Splurge === * {{eat | name=58 Tour Eiffel | alt= | url=http://www.restaurants-toureiffel.com/ | email= | address=Tour Eiffel 1st floor | lat=48.85804 | long=2.29450 | directions=Metro Ecole Militaire | phone=+33 1 76 64 14 64 | tollfree= | fax= | hours=11:30–15:30, 18:30–23:00 | price= | content=The restaurant in the first floor of the Eiffel Tower. One pays of course for the view, not so much for the food. }} * {{eat | name=Gâteaux Thoumieux | alt= | url=http://www.gateauxthoumieux.com/ | email=contact@gateauxthoumieux.com | address=58 rue Saint Dominique | lat=48.859737 | long=2.308663 | directions=Métro La Tour-Maubourg | phone=+33 1 47 05 49 75 | tollfree= | fax= | hours=M-Sa 10:00-20:00, Su 08:30-17:00 | price= | content=Chef patisser Ludovic Chaussard, who had previously worked with Alain Ducasse is designing the cakes. }} * {{eat | name=Le Petit Tibéro | url= | email= | address=132 rue du Bac | lat= | long= | directions= | phone=+33 1 45 48 76 25 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content= }} * {{eat | name=Le Voltaire | url= | email= | address=27, quai Voltaire | lat= | long= | directions= | phone=+33 1 42 61 17 49 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content=Le Voltaire has always been tres chic and with customers like Helene Rochas and the Rothschild family, you know you are dining with the right set. Peaceful wood paneling and lighting that flatters, it is an intimate and romantic setting, where newcomers feel that they belong to an exclusive club. Be sure to dine upon the tenderloin in pepper sauce. }}
